meaning: sign of the ox or cow, 1-3AM, second sign of Chinese zodiac

onyomiExamples.meaning: Fire Ox (14th year of the sexagenary cycle, e.g. 1937, 1997, 2057)
Water Ox (50th year of the sexagenary cycle, e.g. 1913, 1973, 2033)

kunyomiExamples.meaning: the Ox (second sign of the Chinese zodiac), hour of the Ox (around 2am, 1-3am, or 2-4am), north-northeast, twelfth month of the lunar calendar
Metal Ox (38th year of the sexagenary cycle, e.g. 1961, 2021, 2081)
Wood Ox (2nd year of the sexagenary cycle, e.g. 1925, 1985, 2045)
